Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner embedded
More than a third of children aged between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity to 5%.
Obese children come from most families with a lifestyle that is not healthy, according to current research.
It is again demonstrated what the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
On the table, obsessed children feed, for example, of embedded at least twice the frequency of children from normal-weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese had eaten fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence."
In families of overweight children there is no habit of practicing sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for exercise.
A survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and involved almost 900 children of Basic Education from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the “Obsity is not a coincidence” program, which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
A proper diet and sufficient family exercise are determining factors, which make the number of children with overweight and even obesity significantly decreased.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals daily according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," the survey said.
No breakfast but packed for dinner
Experts warn that, in a healthy development, the details are also important, such as, for example, having a fixed hour for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren families breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one is eating breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to discover that in 10% of households nothing is breakfast.
Breakfast is the basis for a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children, crazy fried potatoes are consumed much more often.
Almost all – regardless of weight – drink sweet refreshments daily (70%).
As a rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sports, however, in their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 colleges) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
“The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years, from the point of view of a healthy diet, are far from the ideal.”
Among your favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets.
“It’s above all alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments,” the study’s final report says.
As the main food, the palm is taken with the pasta and the bird meat is followed closely.
Practically, children always refuse legumes and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changes to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
“In the control group of the participants in the study, who filled the questionnaire after completing the prevention program ‘Obesity is not a coincidence’, a significant change was given in many cases in favour of the principles of a healthy diet,” the study notes.
Call attention, for example, about sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer normal and current water.
Children would also often choose bird and fish for the main food in the questionnaire and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
