"We realized that it wasn't so difficult to get to them," says Jamie Bartlett, the main author of a recently published report on European digital populism by the British study center DEMOS.
Facebook’s personal information alloy is so encyclopedic, says Bartlett, that researchers could simply use the advertising tool to determine their desired demographic characteristics with a scientific accuracy – the way that sellers have been using for years.
