As a bassist, what are your influences?
They are so many.
In the first ones I think are Geezer Butler, John Entwistle, C. J. Ramone, John Doe, Paul McCartney, Chuck Dukowski...
There are so many that I could talk all the afternoon about the basists I love.
How has Pearl Jam managed to keep the grunge relevant even though it is no longer a fashion?
I think we all always feel a little disconnected from the word grunge.
When I think about it, it reminds me of the bands I mentioned before, such as Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all those that emerged at the same time, and, if there’s relevance now, I think it’s something wonderful because it’s music that’s worth listening and bands like Mudhoney are now making better music than ever.
At first, his music had a darker content and now it has become more positive.
