The footprints can also discard or reaffirm suspects in cases of murder.
Recently they found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a family could be suspicious of the crime and, effectively, a footprint on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that he has been the murderer, he places him on the scene of the crime.
A CTI dactiloscopist explained that in the objects “the footprints are taken with chemical or physical reactors.”
When they appear, a transplant or tape is used to lift them up.
After this, the impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
