Mr. Deschamps also highlights that the authors of the report seem to give priority to personal autonomy over any other value of society.
Now, he adds that “in society, there are labels and limitations.”
The health law expert Margaret Somerville also expressed her "strong opposition" to the conclusions of the report, which she called a "manifest in favor of euthanasia."
Margaret Somerville, who also belongs to the Royal Society of Canada, puts in judgment especially the lack of abuse in certain countries where euthanasia and assisted suicide are legal, such as in the Netherlands and Oregon.
