The instrument adopted by the Austrian government is closer to the “German model”, since Germany was the first European country to adopt that kind of “rule”.
Before 2017, the structural public deficit should decrease annually by 0.75% of GDP and, from 2017, the structural public deficit of the federal state should not exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while regional states and municipalities should submit balanced budgets.
The objective is, by 2020/2021, that the public debt be reduced under the criterion of 60% set by the Maastricht Treaty.
