Europe, which has long been rejected with regard to the Asia-Pacific region, is gaining ground in the contactless payment sector.
About 26 million Visa bank cards already have this feature, which is accepted at 75,000 payment terminals.
In France, their beginnings are more modest: 400,000 contactless Visa cards are being used.
But the large surfaces work for four.
